        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>light rail transit vehicles [300228566], transit railway vehicles [300228561], rail guideway vehicles [300228410], guideway vehicles [300212494], land vehicles by form [300215717], land vehicles [300212968], vehicles (transportation) [300219258], Transportation Vehicles (hierarchy name) [300042929], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the successors to streetcars, usually larger and faster electric rail transit vehicles capable of boarding and discharging passengers at either track or platform level; often composed of two cars permanently articulated.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor de opvolgers van trams, meestal grotere en snellere elektrische spoorvoertuigen waarbij passagiers in en uit kunnen stappen op spoor- of perronniveau; bestaan vaak uit twee wagons die permanent aan elkaar zijn gekoppeld.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Nachfolger des Straßenbahnwagens, ein gewöhnlich größeres und schnelleres elektrisches Fahrzeug des Schienennahverkehrs, das einen Zustieg und Ausstieg für Fahrgäste sowohl auf Gleishöhe als auch auf Bahnsteighöhe ermöglicht; häufig aus zwei Wagen gebildet, die dauerhaft durch ein Gelenk verbunden sind.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
